WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:00:35.398 --> 00:00:36.718
I think we can all agree

3
00:00:36.797 --> 00:00:39.467
that things were better
under the Empire.

4
00:00:39.602 --> 00:00:43.637
Fortunately. I am still here
to protect you.

5
00:00:43.772 --> 00:00:46.738
Your communities can thrive
under my protection.

6
00:00:47.880 --> 00:00:49.875
You are the lucky few.

7
00:00:50.645 --> 00:00:53.350
But that which I provide
is expensive.

8
00:00:54.153 --> 00:00:56.283
And now
I must maintain all of it

9
00:00:56.418 --> 00:00:57.849
without the Empire's support

10
00:00:57.984 --> 00:01:00.621
until the galaxy realizes
what they've lost

11
00:01:01.190 --> 00:01:03.018
and demand our return.

12
00:01:04.061 --> 00:01:06.494
Long live the Empire.

13
00:01:08.968 --> 00:01:11.400
Long live the Empire.

14
00:01:13.100 --> 00:01:14.337
Good.

15
00:01:15.138 --> 00:01:16.603
Now for the bad news.

16
00:01:18.406 --> 00:01:20.444
I am raising your tribute.

17
00:01:23.178 --> 00:01:24.579
But...

18
00:01:24.715 --> 00:01:28.417
But. Your Excellency.
we are operating at a loss.

19
00:01:29.853 --> 00:01:33.020
The trade routes are plagued
with pirates and thieves.

20
00:01:33.155 --> 00:01:34.187
ready to attack at

21
00:01:38.398 --> 00:01:40.825
Are you saying
that my protection is lacking?

22
00:01:41.428 --> 00:01:43.729
No. Your Excellency.

23
00:01:45.300 --> 00:01:47.606
I-I am saying that. uh

24
00:01:51.873 --> 00:01:55.213
Perhaps you should all go
back to your townships

25
00:01:55.816 --> 00:01:57.578
and focus on solutions.

26
00:01:58.652 --> 00:02:00.218
not excuses.

27
00:02:01.988 --> 00:02:03.485
Does that sound reasonable?

28
00:02:08.724 --> 00:02:10.556
Sounds like a perimeter alarm.

29
00:02:10.692 --> 00:02:12.989
I'll confirm.

30
00:02:15.159 --> 00:02:17.296
- I've lost contact.
- Go check it.

31
00:02:20.406 --> 00:02:21.912
There's nothing to worry about.

32
00:02:21.936 --> 00:02:24.539
I'll send for reinforcements.

33
00:02:28.579 --> 00:02:30.459
I will require
a revenue projection...

34
00:02:53.068 --> 00:02:55.347
<i>We need backup. On the double!</i>

35
00:02:55.371 --> 00:02:56.604
Code Red.

36
00:03:03.774 --> 00:03:05.074
Lay down cover fire.

37
00:03:07.087 --> 00:03:08.517
Take up arms!

38
00:03:22.265 --> 00:03:24.335
Long live the Empire!

39
00:05:07.406 --> 00:05:10.001
What are you waiting for?
Hop on.

40
00:05:26.155 --> 00:05:27.418
Hang on.

41
00:05:53.986 --> 00:05:55.110
Did we get him?

42
00:05:55.246 --> 00:05:56.646
Not yet. sir.
But we will.

43
00:06:04.590 --> 00:06:07.458
- We missed him! He's under us.
<i>- We have him.</i>

44
00:06:07.593 --> 00:06:08.631
<i>Fire.</i>

45
00:06:53.440 --> 00:06:55.445
<i>What's going on?
Give me a status report.</i>

46
00:06:55.581 --> 00:06:57.308
<i>Has the target been eliminated?</i>

47
00:06:57.444 --> 00:06:59.781
- We've lost contact.
- Walker Three is gone.

48
00:06:59.916 --> 00:07:02.217
- <i>Send everybody!</i>
- Understood.

49
00:07:02.352 --> 00:07:03.646
Prepare to engage!

50
00:07:12.429 --> 00:07:13.429
Get ready. Weapons up.

51
00:07:13.564 --> 00:07:15.390
Full barrel. Now. let's go.

52
00:07:50.197 --> 00:07:51.669
<i>Give me a status update.</i>

53
00:07:51.804 --> 00:07:54.429
<i>Did you see him?
Have you located him?</i>

54
00:07:55.573 --> 00:07:56.864
<i>Did you get The Mandalorian?</i>

55
00:07:59.136 --> 00:08:00.369
Something's up there.

56
00:08:02.281 --> 00:08:03.714
He's on the roof!

57
00:08:04.250 --> 00:08:05.474
<i>Can you see him?</i>

58
00:08:05.976 --> 00:08:06.976
<i>Take him out!</i>

59
00:08:07.054 --> 00:08:08.245
Get up there.

60
00:08:08.881 --> 00:08:10.047
But we're pilots.

61
00:08:10.183 --> 00:08:12.748
- Go now! Do it!
- Yes. sir. On our way.

62
00:08:12.884 --> 00:08:14.383
Get up there.

63
00:08:15.295 --> 00:08:16.335
Set the charges.

64
00:08:16.462 --> 00:08:18.194
- Prepare for exfil.
- Sir.

65
00:08:18.329 --> 00:08:21.500
<i>He's breaching the hatch.
He's breaching the hatch!</i>

66
00:08:39.052 --> 00:08:40.277
Autopilot.

67
00:09:12.982 --> 00:09:15.147
I know. I know.
I need to get the shot.

68
00:09:45.018 --> 00:09:47.751
You know. it's better
if you bring 'em in alive.

69
00:09:54.787 --> 00:09:56.023
You okay?

70
00:09:58.289 --> 00:10:00.391
You see. you catch the bad guy

71
00:10:00.526 --> 00:10:03.466
and they tell us
where the other bad guys are.

72
00:10:03.602 --> 00:10:05.637
Things went a little sideways.

73
00:12:26.307 --> 00:12:29.374
Good luck.
You're gonna need it.

74
00:12:37.720 --> 00:12:40.486
Messy. Very messy.

75
00:12:41.489 --> 00:12:44.424
It was the best I could do
under the circumstances.

76
00:12:45.194 --> 00:12:47.757
The problem is.
we need information.

77
00:12:47.893 --> 00:12:49.895
Without it. we're never gonna
get to the bottom of

78
00:12:50.031 --> 00:12:51.830
what the Empire's up to.

79
00:12:51.965 --> 00:12:53.399
Just give me time.

80
00:12:53.535 --> 00:12:55.475
I'll take out every bad guy
in your deck of cards.

81
00:12:55.499 --> 00:12:57.402
This isn't about revenge.

82
00:12:57.537 --> 00:13:00.471
It's about
preventing another war...

83
00:13:03.447 --> 00:13:05.874
and protecting everything
the Rebellion fought for.

84
00:13:06.010 --> 00:13:08.611
Does that mean I'm not
getting paid for this one?

85
00:13:10.217 --> 00:13:12.014
You're getting paid all right.

86
00:13:12.150 --> 00:13:13.385
Come with me.

87
00:13:22.427 --> 00:13:23.587
Impressive.

88
00:13:23.694 --> 00:13:25.562
Where did you get one of these?

89
00:13:25.697 --> 00:13:27.729
It was from
a captured Imperial commandant

90
00:13:27.864 --> 00:13:30.533
who had a big collection
of vintage vehicles.

91
00:13:30.669 --> 00:13:33.973
This one is stock.
Perfectly restored.

92
00:13:34.109 --> 00:13:36.208
I took it out for a test spin.

93
00:13:36.344 --> 00:13:38.476
They did a nice job
on the rebuild.

94
00:13:40.812 --> 00:13:42.716
This is worth a lot more than

95
00:13:42.852 --> 00:13:44.352
the bounty on that Imp.

96
00:13:44.488 --> 00:13:47.254
Well. let's call it an advance
on the next mission.

97
00:13:49.220 --> 00:13:50.521
What next mission?

98
00:13:51.056 --> 00:13:52.655
Commander Coin.

99
00:13:53.424 --> 00:13:55.262
Our missing Ace of Staves.

100
00:13:57.364 --> 00:13:59.032
No one knows what he looks like

101
00:13:59.168 --> 00:14:01.631
and most believe him to be dead.

102
00:14:01.766 --> 00:14:04.504
Not a lot to go on.
What's the play?

103
00:14:04.640 --> 00:14:08.306
I want you to go to Nal Hutta
and meet with the Hutts.

104
00:14:08.442 --> 00:14:10.339
They've agreed to
lead us to him.

105
00:14:10.474 --> 00:14:11.807
What's in it for them?

106
00:14:11.942 --> 00:14:14.347
Their nephew's being held
against his will

107
00:14:14.483 --> 00:14:17.016
by another crime syndicate
on the Outer Rim.

108
00:14:17.151 --> 00:14:18.316
and they need a professional

109
00:14:18.452 --> 00:14:19.983
to get him out
quickly and quietly.

110
00:14:20.118 --> 00:14:21.386
Where is he?

111
00:14:21.521 --> 00:14:23.323
They'll only tell you in person.

112
00:14:23.957 --> 00:14:25.387
You got a name?

113
00:14:25.522 --> 00:14:27.163
His name is Rotta the Hutt.

114
00:14:27.299 --> 00:14:31.160
The only surviving heir
of crime lord Jabba the Hutt.

115
00:14:31.296 --> 00:14:32.633
You ever cross his path?

116
00:14:32.768 --> 00:14:34.499
I tried not to.

117
00:14:35.638 --> 00:14:36.666
So...

118
00:14:37.367 --> 00:14:38.568
do we have a deal?

119
00:14:38.703 --> 00:14:40.739
I only hunt down
Imperial war criminals.

120
00:14:40.875 --> 00:14:44.344
I don't work for gangsters
anymore. especially the Hutts.

121
00:14:44.479 --> 00:14:47.016
That's right. you don't.
You work for us.

122
00:14:47.152 --> 00:14:50.416
And right now. this is
what we need you to do.

123
00:14:50.551 --> 00:14:53.749
You don't want the job.
I got nothing for you.

124
00:15:05.362 --> 00:15:06.630
Come aboard.

125
00:15:08.568 --> 00:15:10.667
May as well have a look around.

126
00:15:15.408 --> 00:15:17.376
Let's go hear the Hutts out.

127
00:15:17.511 --> 00:15:20.015
I'll even let you fly this time.

128
00:15:20.151 --> 00:15:22.018
I didn't say yes.

129
00:15:22.153 --> 00:15:23.612
You didn't say no either.

130
00:15:46.176 --> 00:15:48.540
She's stock. but she's clean.

131
00:16:05.193 --> 00:16:06.927
Hey.

132
00:16:07.063 --> 00:16:08.730
Don't touch anything.

133
00:16:08.866 --> 00:16:10.364
Never touch the buttons.

134
00:17:53.669 --> 00:17:56.096
<i>Identify yourself.</i>

135
00:17:57.133 --> 00:17:59.440
<i>Razor Crest.</i>
requesting clearance.

136
00:17:59.575 --> 00:18:02.444
I'm here
by invitation of the Twins.

137
00:18:02.579 --> 00:18:06.216
Easy on the sticks.
They're expecting us.

138
00:18:06.785 --> 00:18:08.218
We should be fine.

139
00:18:10.312 --> 00:18:12.112
<i>Clearance granted.</i>

140
00:18:12.156 --> 00:18:14.190
<i>You are clear to approach.</i>

141
00:18:14.325 --> 00:18:16.292
They've got
a lot of firepower here.

142
00:18:16.428 --> 00:18:19.458
Yeah. Looks like
they hired the Droid Gotra.

143
00:18:19.593 --> 00:18:22.023
The Hutts
take security seriously.

144
00:19:12.649 --> 00:19:14.689
The Hutts have been the
head of criminal enterprises

145
00:19:14.777 --> 00:19:16.979
for thousands of years.

146
00:19:20.624 --> 00:19:22.726
They use violence and treachery

147
00:19:22.862 --> 00:19:24.261
to maintain control.

148
00:19:25.830 --> 00:19:27.088
Be careful.

149
00:19:27.223 --> 00:19:32.093
We may be their guests.
but we are not safe.

150
00:20:27.492 --> 00:20:29.058
I don't work for you.

151
00:20:29.193 --> 00:20:30.822
I work for the New Republic.

152
00:20:31.492 --> 00:20:32.624
I'm told you can lead us

153
00:20:32.760 --> 00:20:35.299
to the Imperial fugitive
Commander Coin.

154
00:20:38.229 --> 00:20:39.989
I understand your nephew. Rotta.

155
00:20:40.104 --> 00:20:41.672
has been kidnapped.

156
00:20:52.110 --> 00:20:54.844
Think of how you would feel

157
00:20:54.980 --> 00:20:58.246
if your little one went missing.

158
00:21:00.289 --> 00:21:01.826
What does he look like?

159
00:21:01.961 --> 00:21:03.419
Do you have an image?

160
00:21:19.907 --> 00:21:23.704
Okay.
I'll rescue your nephew.

161
00:21:23.840 --> 00:21:25.008
Where is he being held?

162
00:21:30.948 --> 00:21:32.521
It shall be done.

163
00:21:51.708 --> 00:21:53.636
We're about to
come out of hyperspace

164
00:21:53.771 --> 00:21:55.404
in the Shakari system.

165
00:21:55.539 --> 00:21:57.725
<i>To state
the obvious. you are operating</i>

166
00:21:57.749 --> 00:21:59.949
<i>outside the jurisdiction
of the New Republic.</i>

167
00:22:00.952 --> 00:22:05.548
If things get messy. I can't
call in an X-wing strike.

168
00:22:05.683 --> 00:22:07.120
I know the drill.

169
00:22:08.090 --> 00:22:11.726
Before going into harm's way.
check your armor first.

170
00:22:11.861 --> 00:22:14.365
It's gotta fit snug
so it doesn't slide.

171
00:22:14.500 --> 00:22:17.434
but not so tight that it
restricts your movement.

172
00:22:17.968 --> 00:22:19.033
Got it?

173
00:22:20.503 --> 00:22:22.340
How's that feel?

174
00:22:45.858 --> 00:22:47.728
All right. Zeb. drop us here.

175
00:23:44.153 --> 00:23:45.589
Yes?

176
00:23:45.725 --> 00:23:47.126
I'll take a flat-meat fry
for the little one.

177
00:23:47.150 --> 00:23:48.849
Got it. Okay. got it. got it.

178
00:23:48.985 --> 00:23:50.593
Flat-meat fry. huh?

179
00:23:52.730 --> 00:23:54.410
Yeah. yeah. yeah. yeah. yeah.

180
00:24:00.797 --> 00:24:02.266
Whoa.

181
00:24:02.401 --> 00:24:03.883
That's quite an
impressive denomination.

182
00:24:03.907 --> 00:24:05.387
I'm not sure I've got
change for that.

183
00:24:05.468 --> 00:24:06.782
You can keep the change.

184
00:24:06.806 --> 00:24:08.244
I'm new to these parts.

185
00:24:08.379 --> 00:24:10.407
I can use some information.

186
00:24:10.542 --> 00:24:13.281
Yeah. for this price. I'll
tell you whatever you want.

187
00:24:13.417 --> 00:24:14.849
I'm looking for a Hutt.

188
00:24:14.985 --> 00:24:17.345
Shh. Don't mention that name.
Don't say that.

189
00:24:17.480 --> 00:24:19.062
What. are you trying
to get us both killed?

190
00:24:19.086 --> 00:24:21.651
Here. Keep your credits.
Food's on me.

191
00:24:21.787 --> 00:24:23.353
Go away. Thank you.

192
00:24:23.489 --> 00:24:26.089
Okay. never happened.
Let's go. Nothing to see here.

193
00:24:26.224 --> 00:24:27.698
Damn Mandalorian.
talking like that.

194
00:24:27.833 --> 00:24:29.899
Just out in the open.
he talks like... What is this?

195
00:24:30.034 --> 00:24:32.701
No. no. no. No. no. no. no.
I don't want your credits.

196
00:24:32.836 --> 00:24:34.499
'cause I didn't give you
any information.

197
00:24:34.634 --> 00:24:36.199
His name is Rotta.

198
00:24:36.876 --> 00:24:37.876
Really?

199
00:24:40.111 --> 00:24:41.235
Something funny?

200
00:24:41.371 --> 00:24:42.873
Yeah. yeah.
Everybody...

201
00:24:43.008 --> 00:24:44.613
Everybody knows Rotta the Hutt.

202
00:24:44.748 --> 00:24:47.243
That guy's a monster.

203
00:25:33.232 --> 00:25:34.554
Rotta! Rotta! Rotta!

204
00:25:34.690 --> 00:25:37.161
He doesn't seem like
a prisoner to me.

205
00:25:38.804 --> 00:25:40.769
Rotta!

206
00:26:23.275 --> 00:26:25.242
I'm here to rescue you.

207
00:26:27.114 --> 00:26:29.345
What makes you think
I need rescuing?

208
00:26:29.480 --> 00:26:31.316
Your aunt and uncle
hired me to find you.

209
00:26:33.048 --> 00:26:36.927
Yeah. I see. Well. thank you.
but I don't require rescuing.

210
00:26:37.063 --> 00:26:39.724
Tomorrow's the last match
in my contract and after that.

211
00:26:39.859 --> 00:26:41.356
my debt will be paid.

212
00:26:41.491 --> 00:26:43.458
I'll be a free agent.

213
00:26:46.765 --> 00:26:47.970
Paid to who?

214
00:26:50.902 --> 00:26:52.137
Who's he?

215
00:26:53.007 --> 00:26:54.610
Don't stare.

216
00:26:54.745 --> 00:26:56.645
It's okay. What's your name?

217
00:26:56.781 --> 00:26:58.841
He doesn't talk.

218
00:26:58.977 --> 00:27:00.611
Who do you have to pay?

219
00:27:00.746 --> 00:27:01.986
Can I feed him?

220
00:27:06.058 --> 00:27:07.157
Sure.

221
00:27:07.293 --> 00:27:09.055
Who do you have to pay?

222
00:27:14.661 --> 00:27:16.227
Lord Janu.

223
00:27:17.293 --> 00:27:18.893
I don't know the name.

224
00:27:19.028 --> 00:27:20.463
You should.

225
00:27:20.599 --> 00:27:23.432
He runs the Syndicate
on all the moons of Shakari.

226
00:27:25.906 --> 00:27:27.171
He signed me to his stable.

227
00:27:27.306 --> 00:27:29.575
He bankrolled
my board and training.

228
00:27:29.711 --> 00:27:31.544
He keeps you in a cage.

229
00:27:31.679 --> 00:27:32.915
He treats me well.

230
00:27:33.051 --> 00:27:35.752
And after tomorrow night.
I'll be my own man.

231
00:27:35.887 --> 00:27:38.685
And with the following
he got me as a promoter.

232
00:27:38.821 --> 00:27:40.820
not only will my debt be paid.

233
00:27:40.956 --> 00:27:42.283
but I'll be rich
by the solstice.

234
00:27:42.418 --> 00:27:44.761
Grogu. heel!

235
00:27:47.360 --> 00:27:50.195
Don't worry. I'm not my father.

236
00:27:55.335 --> 00:27:57.574
You know how hard it is
to be your own man

237
00:27:57.710 --> 00:28:00.040
when your father is
Jabba the Hutt?

238
00:28:05.279 --> 00:28:07.742
You see them
cheering for me out there?

239
00:28:07.878 --> 00:28:09.448
For me.

240
00:28:09.583 --> 00:28:12.579
It's the first time
I'm not living in his shadow.

241
00:28:12.714 --> 00:28:15.218
That's why I fight in the pits.

242
00:28:15.354 --> 00:28:19.026
They feared him.
but they cheer for me.

243
00:28:20.628 --> 00:28:22.257
So. no...

244
00:28:22.392 --> 00:28:24.896
I don't need to be rescued.

245
00:28:28.298 --> 00:28:30.334
Where can I find Lord Janu?

246
00:28:31.667 --> 00:28:33.777
Thank you.
Closed for the night.

247
00:28:38.413 --> 00:28:40.477
What the hell's he thinking?
Damn Mandalorians.

248
00:28:40.612 --> 00:28:42.324
Mandalorians. they don't even
come from here.

249
00:28:42.348 --> 00:28:44.251
He's going around. talking

250
00:28:45.221 --> 00:28:48.153
I just wanna know
where I can find Lord Janu.

251
00:28:48.289 --> 00:28:51.623
Don't say that.
Do not say that name.

252
00:28:51.758 --> 00:28:53.121
Stop saying it.

253
00:28:53.257 --> 00:28:55.659
I recommend you calm down.

254
00:28:55.795 --> 00:28:57.539
Just. please. please.
don't kill me. Don't kill me.

255
00:28:57.563 --> 00:28:59.364
I've got... I've got
12 little ones at home.

256
00:28:59.499 --> 00:29:01.763
smaller than him.
It's... They're smaller.

257
00:29:02.399 --> 00:29:04.300
Yeah. it's just...

258
00:29:04.436 --> 00:29:06.869
I pay him protection. okay?

259
00:29:07.004 --> 00:29:08.172
We all do.

260
00:29:08.308 --> 00:29:09.748
I barely make a living.
to be honest.

261
00:29:09.806 --> 00:29:11.815
- But at least I'm alive.
- Who collects for him?

262
00:29:11.951 --> 00:29:13.676
I don't know.
Different people come in.

263
00:29:13.812 --> 00:29:15.972
Sometimes they come here.
sometimes I do a drop myself.

264
00:29:16.082 --> 00:29:17.447
- What do I know?
- Where?

265
00:29:17.582 --> 00:29:20.284
- Where what?
- Where do you do the drops?

266
00:29:20.419 --> 00:29:21.782
I don't... Some pla...
Sometimes.

267
00:29:21.917 --> 00:29:23.757
I go down to...
different places.

268
00:29:23.786 --> 00:29:25.890
Usually... Sometimes
I go to the salt bar

269
00:29:26.025 --> 00:29:27.590
under Korvin Station.

270
00:29:27.725 --> 00:29:29.633
And then there's
other places too. You go to...

271
00:29:29.769 --> 00:29:31.630
You know. You know.
I go around.

272
00:29:33.169 --> 00:29:35.002
No. I don't want it.
I don't want it.

273
00:29:35.138 --> 00:29:36.600
I didn't give you
any information.

274
00:29:36.735 --> 00:29:38.805
- I was just talking.
- That's not for information.

275
00:29:38.940 --> 00:29:40.338
It's to cover his tab.

276
00:30:25.955 --> 00:30:27.550
I'm looking for Lord Janu.

277
00:30:32.059 --> 00:30:34.227
Maybe you made a mistake.

278
00:30:35.759 --> 00:30:38.726
Maybe you remember wrong
and think you know me.

279
00:30:41.930 --> 00:30:44.501
Maybe you just walked through
the wrong door.

280
00:30:45.570 --> 00:30:48.307
Well. I'm not here to buy salt.

281
00:30:48.907 --> 00:30:50.276
Salt?

282
00:30:50.946 --> 00:30:52.410
We don't sell salt.

283
00:30:53.146 --> 00:30:54.478
It's on the ration.

284
00:30:56.613 --> 00:30:58.750
How much for the shoulder candy?

285
00:31:01.520 --> 00:31:03.652
Would look real pretty
in a cage.

286
00:31:04.488 --> 00:31:06.457
I'm here to see Lord Janu.

287
00:31:07.458 --> 00:31:09.757
I won't repeat myself again.

288
00:31:58.379 --> 00:32:01.017
It seems you've
earned your salt today.

289
00:32:03.918 --> 00:32:04.979
I'm Janu.

290
00:32:05.815 --> 00:32:08.223
Come to the back
and pick out a crystal.

291
00:32:08.592 --> 00:32:09.619
Hogsbreth.

292
00:32:11.256 --> 00:32:13.128
have the boys clean up.

293
00:32:14.131 --> 00:32:16.429
Make sure I don't lose any pets.

294
00:32:34.947 --> 00:32:36.184
Here.

295
00:32:36.785 --> 00:32:38.087
Choose one.

296
00:32:38.222 --> 00:32:40.386
Salt is of no value to me
where I'm from.

297
00:32:40.521 --> 00:32:42.455
But here
it's worth a small fortune.

298
00:32:42.590 --> 00:32:46.228
because it's rationed
by the politicians.

299
00:32:46.764 --> 00:32:48.394
Which makes it rare.

300
00:32:49.734 --> 00:32:51.496
As are you. Mandalorian.

301
00:32:52.731 --> 00:32:54.933
Have you ever considered
fighting in the pits?

302
00:32:55.069 --> 00:32:57.304
I try to avoid violence.

303
00:32:58.610 --> 00:33:00.010
'Course you do.

304
00:33:00.777 --> 00:33:02.177
I do as well.

305
00:33:03.610 --> 00:33:05.245
So what brings you to
this establishment

306
00:33:05.381 --> 00:33:06.943
if you're not
in the market for salt?

307
00:33:07.078 --> 00:33:10.451
I wanna buy out the contract
on a fighter from your stable.

308
00:33:10.586 --> 00:33:13.551
Perhaps you would consider
joining my stable instead?

309
00:33:19.460 --> 00:33:22.027
This buys a lot of salt
where I'm from.

310
00:33:22.162 --> 00:33:23.695
I am offering you this

311
00:33:23.831 --> 00:33:26.135
in exchange for the fighting
contract on Rotta the Hutt.

312
00:33:26.271 --> 00:33:28.234
My dear boy.
there's no price high enough

313
00:33:28.370 --> 00:33:30.405
to buy him out of
his last fights.

314
00:33:30.541 --> 00:33:32.661
I've been grooming that
little prince for many cycles.

315
00:33:32.770 --> 00:33:34.406
setting him up
for tomorrow's match.

316
00:33:34.541 --> 00:33:35.946
Take the credits.

317
00:33:36.081 --> 00:33:38.246
It's his last fight
for you anyway.

318
00:33:39.148 --> 00:33:40.512
It's his last fight ever.

319
00:33:41.780 --> 00:33:43.340
I've collected
the most deadly creatures

320
00:33:43.414 --> 00:33:45.316
from across the galaxy.

321
00:33:45.452 --> 00:33:47.651
He's fighting a Dejarik match?

322
00:33:48.053 --> 00:33:49.357
Yes.

323
00:33:49.926 --> 00:33:51.622
He will die tomorrow.

324
00:33:52.523 --> 00:33:54.362
And a select few know it.

325
00:33:55.031 --> 00:33:56.528
Here's my gift to you:

326
00:33:57.329 --> 00:33:58.563
take those credits.

327
00:33:59.698 --> 00:34:01.995
bet it all
on the death of the Hutt.

328
00:34:02.673 --> 00:34:03.899
In exchange.

329
00:34:04.035 --> 00:34:07.440
all I ask is that you
consider fighting in my pit.

330
00:34:07.575 --> 00:34:09.845
The people of Shakari
would pay any price

331
00:34:09.980 --> 00:34:11.609
to see the rarest of sights.

332
00:34:11.744 --> 00:34:14.683
one of the legendary
Mandalorian warriors

333
00:34:14.819 --> 00:34:17.351
engaging in blood sport.

334
00:34:25.864 --> 00:34:27.525
This should more than cover

335
00:34:27.661 --> 00:34:30.067
our little misunderstanding
out there.

336
00:34:33.601 --> 00:34:36.139
All I ask
is that you consider my offer.

337
00:34:37.470 --> 00:34:40.143
Could make us both very rich.

338
00:35:13.941 --> 00:35:17.246
Looks like we're gonna have to
do this the hard way.

339
00:36:45.802 --> 00:36:47.327
What?

340
00:36:48.130 --> 00:36:49.729
Janu's planning on killing you.

341
00:36:49.865 --> 00:36:50.906
I'm here to get you out.

342
00:36:54.042 --> 00:36:57.103
Tomorrow's my last fight.
I'll be free after I win.

343
00:36:57.238 --> 00:37:00.447
The fix is in.
It's a Dejarik match.

344
00:37:00.583 --> 00:37:02.443
He will keep
throwing opponents at you

345
00:37:02.579 --> 00:37:03.380
until you die.

346
00:37:03.516 --> 00:37:05.587
Why should I believe you?

347
00:37:05.722 --> 00:37:08.120
You were sent by my aunt
and uncle who want me dead.

348
00:37:08.256 --> 00:37:09.882
They want you back.

349
00:37:10.018 --> 00:37:11.323
You're embarrassing them.

350
00:37:11.459 --> 00:37:12.659
The Twins want me dead

351
00:37:12.792 --> 00:37:15.194
because I'm heir
to the throne. not them.

352
00:37:15.330 --> 00:37:16.695
But I don't want it.

353
00:37:16.830 --> 00:37:19.360
I don't wanna be anything
like my father.

354
00:37:20.363 --> 00:37:23.367
When I first started fighting.
the people all booed me.

355
00:37:23.503 --> 00:37:24.802
They wanted to see me die

356
00:37:24.937 --> 00:37:27.143
because I'm the son
of Jabba the Hutt.

357
00:37:27.279 --> 00:37:29.045
Then I won and became a champion

358
00:37:29.180 --> 00:37:31.181
and they slowly began to cheer.

359
00:37:31.316 --> 00:37:33.211
They realized I'm not my father.

360
00:37:33.346 --> 00:37:34.747
I'm my own man.

361
00:37:34.882 --> 00:37:37.144
and I'm not afraid to fight
for what I have.

362
00:37:37.279 --> 00:37:39.986
To earn it.
To prove myself to everyone.

363
00:37:40.889 --> 00:37:43.717
Kid. fighting's not a sport.

364
00:37:43.853 --> 00:37:45.459
It's a last resort.

365
00:37:45.594 --> 00:37:47.787
Now come with me
before things get ugly.

366
00:37:47.923 --> 00:37:50.130
Guards. he's back!

367
00:37:53.764 --> 00:37:56.706
Get out. Get out!

368
00:38:41.745 --> 00:38:43.909
Rotta! Rotta! Rotta!

369
00:39:04.042 --> 00:39:06.200
<i>Rotta!</i>

370
00:39:33.029 --> 00:39:34.604
I don't want to fight you.

371
00:39:35.307 --> 00:39:37.672
Then you're in for a long day!

372
00:39:46.874 --> 00:39:47.874
Yes!

373
00:40:13.743 --> 00:40:16.144
I'm not going to kill you.

374
00:40:16.280 --> 00:40:17.977
I'm here to rescue you.

375
00:41:04.627 --> 00:41:06.996
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill!

376
00:41:07.132 --> 00:41:09.823
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill!

377
00:41:09.959 --> 00:41:12.391
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill!

378
00:41:12.527 --> 00:41:15.301
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill!

379
00:41:15.437 --> 00:41:17.671
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill!

380
00:41:17.807 --> 00:41:19.742
Kill! Kill! Kill...

381
00:41:19.878 --> 00:41:20.933
I yield.

382
00:41:25.678 --> 00:41:27.645
Rotta the Hutt has won.

383
00:41:27.780 --> 00:41:30.553
Now you owe him his freedom.

384
00:41:37.355 --> 00:41:39.661
Rotta the Hutt has won.

385
00:41:40.230 --> 00:41:42.389
Now he is free...

386
00:41:44.903 --> 00:41:45.927
to die!

387
00:42:31.616 --> 00:42:34.650
Our only chance
is to work together.

388
00:43:58.936 --> 00:44:00.643
Watch out for the little one.

389
00:44:00.667 --> 00:44:02.296
Yeah. I got this.

390
00:45:12.970 --> 00:45:13.970
We should go now.

391
00:45:14.035 --> 00:45:15.404
Now!

392
00:45:45.607 --> 00:45:46.635
Are you good?

393
00:45:47.805 --> 00:45:50.571
Don't worry. buddy.
We're getting out of here.

394
00:46:13.264 --> 00:46:15.361
You were right.
The fix was in.

395
00:46:15.497 --> 00:46:16.997
Let's get you out of here.

396
00:46:18.874 --> 00:46:20.601
I'm gonna find us a ride.

397
00:46:42.796 --> 00:46:43.926
Sorry. Mando.

398
00:46:44.061 --> 00:46:45.659
I can't go back.

399
00:47:08.922 --> 00:47:11.025
Zeb. I got a runner.

400
00:48:01.171 --> 00:48:03.539
Okay. you got me.

401
00:48:04.375 --> 00:48:06.509
Can't blame a guy for trying.

402
00:48:24.092 --> 00:48:26.392
We're about
to jump to hyperspace.

403
00:48:26.528 --> 00:48:28.002
Where are you bringing me?

404
00:48:28.138 --> 00:48:30.405
It's not safe
to keep you chained up.

405
00:48:30.540 --> 00:48:31.540
If I unlock you.

406
00:48:31.568 --> 00:48:33.468
can we agree to no funny stuff?

407
00:48:33.604 --> 00:48:35.774
Are you bringing me
to Nal Hutta?

408
00:48:35.910 --> 00:48:37.043
This is an old ship.

409
00:48:37.179 --> 00:48:39.278
Sometimes things
get a little bouncy.

410
00:48:39.414 --> 00:48:41.575
My aunt and uncle
were scared of my father.

411
00:48:41.711 --> 00:48:43.645
They've always been cruel to me.

412
00:48:43.780 --> 00:48:46.015
Now that they control
his criminal empire.

413
00:48:46.151 --> 00:48:47.615
they need me eliminated.

414
00:48:47.751 --> 00:48:49.954
You bring me to them.
I'm a dead man.

415
00:48:50.090 --> 00:48:51.090
You don't know that.

416
00:48:51.190 --> 00:48:52.389
If you let me go.

417
00:48:52.524 --> 00:48:54.262
you'll never hear from me again.

418
00:48:54.732 --> 00:48:56.398
It's a big galaxy.

419
00:48:56.533 --> 00:48:57.630
I can disappear.

420
00:48:57.765 --> 00:48:59.226
Sorry. kid.

421
00:48:59.362 --> 00:49:01.366
I was hired to do a job.

422
00:49:01.501 --> 00:49:03.804
I don't know how
you sleep at night.

423
00:49:03.939 --> 00:49:05.904
working for those monsters.

424
00:49:06.040 --> 00:49:07.841
I don't work for them.

425
00:49:07.976 --> 00:49:09.942
I work for the New Republic.

426
00:49:10.078 --> 00:49:12.641
They hired me. not the Twins.

427
00:49:12.777 --> 00:49:14.410
When I bring you back.
they're giving me

428
00:49:14.545 --> 00:49:16.251
the whereabouts
of Commander Coin.

429
00:49:16.387 --> 00:49:19.819
a high-ranking ex-Imperial
operating on the Outer Rim.

430
00:49:19.955 --> 00:49:21.387
It's Janu.

431
00:49:22.290 --> 00:49:25.119
The man you're looking for
is Janu.

432
00:49:25.254 --> 00:49:26.821
Lord Janu Coin.

433
00:49:26.956 --> 00:49:28.663
That's who the Hutts
are gonna give you.

434
00:49:28.798 --> 00:49:30.198
He's ex-Imperial.

435
00:49:30.333 --> 00:49:32.294
That can't be.
The Twins would've told me.

436
00:49:32.429 --> 00:49:34.369
I saw stormtroopers.

437
00:49:35.072 --> 00:49:36.704
He brought me to his estate once

438
00:49:36.839 --> 00:49:38.039
to celebrate a big win

439
00:49:38.174 --> 00:49:39.901
and there were
stormtroopers everywhere.

440
00:49:40.037 --> 00:49:42.140
If you don't believe me
and you don't get him now.

441
00:49:42.275 --> 00:49:44.078
you won't get another shot.

442
00:49:44.214 --> 00:49:46.114
In fact.
it might already be too late.

443
00:49:46.817 --> 00:49:48.177
That's quite a story.

444
00:49:48.313 --> 00:49:49.879
Why should I believe you?

445
00:49:50.014 --> 00:49:53.418
You're a bounty hunter.
you know when someone's lying.

446
00:49:55.692 --> 00:49:57.087
Am I lying...

447
00:49:57.223 --> 00:49:59.193
or am I telling the truth?

448
00:50:19.707 --> 00:50:21.147
That's it.

449
00:50:21.282 --> 00:50:23.045
That's Janu Coin's compound.

450
00:50:23.881 --> 00:50:26.483
Could be big boy's
telling the truth.

451
00:50:26.619 --> 00:50:29.586
The place is lousy
with stormtroopers.

452
00:50:32.724 --> 00:50:34.136
How many did you see

453
00:50:34.160 --> 00:50:35.394
when you were in there?

454
00:50:36.128 --> 00:50:37.128
A lot.

455
00:50:38.498 --> 00:50:39.861
You're gonna need
a lot of backup

456
00:50:39.996 --> 00:50:41.631
if you're actually
thinking of going in.

457
00:50:42.539 --> 00:50:43.667
Uh-huh.

458
00:50:44.670 --> 00:50:46.775
Get word
to all our foot soldiers

459
00:50:46.910 --> 00:50:48.574
on the dark side of Shakari.

460
00:50:48.710 --> 00:50:52.471
I want eyes on the starport
and all the freight lanes.

461
00:50:52.606 --> 00:50:53.776
Lean on the mayor.

462
00:50:53.911 --> 00:50:55.874
Nothing takes off
or lands until we find them.

463
00:50:56.010 --> 00:50:58.451
Muster
my personal security forces.

464
00:50:58.587 --> 00:51:00.889
We're going to hit the streets
in full armor.

465
00:51:01.025 --> 00:51:02.265
I don't want to take any chances

466
00:51:02.289 --> 00:51:03.687
when it comes to
The Mandalorian.

467
00:51:03.822 --> 00:51:06.357
I've heard many things
about those monsters.

468
00:51:06.493 --> 00:51:08.196
It's all true.

469
00:51:09.362 --> 00:51:11.430
Imperial Commander Janu Coin.

470
00:51:11.565 --> 00:51:13.294
I'm here on behalf
of the New Republic

471
00:51:13.430 --> 00:51:15.435
to bring you to justice.

472
00:51:15.571 --> 00:51:18.404
I'm afraid we're outside
of your jurisdiction.

473
00:51:18.972 --> 00:51:20.138
Take him!

474
00:51:25.081 --> 00:51:26.648
- Set blasters on full.
- Hurry!

475
00:52:25.976 --> 00:52:28.067
I can bring you in warm...

476
00:52:29.309 --> 00:52:31.477
or I can bring you in cold.

477
00:52:55.239 --> 00:52:56.577
<i>Grogu.</i>

478
00:52:58.173 --> 00:52:59.505
<i>Rotta.</i>

479
00:53:00.041 --> 00:53:01.337
<i>Rotta. come in.</i>

480
00:53:01.473 --> 00:53:02.910
<i>Does anyone read me?</i>

481
00:53:04.409 --> 00:53:05.876
I'm up. I'm up.

482
00:53:06.012 --> 00:53:08.027
<i>I need you
to fire up the drives.</i>

483
00:53:08.051 --> 00:53:09.183
<i>Fire up the drives.</i>

484
00:53:09.319 --> 00:53:11.451
- <i>We have company.</i>
- Received.

485
00:53:11.587 --> 00:53:14.280
I don't know how to fly.
Do you know how to fly?

486
00:53:14.883 --> 00:53:16.357
Neither of us know how to fly.

487
00:53:16.492 --> 00:53:18.491
and I can't even
fit in the cockpit.

488
00:53:24.665 --> 00:53:28.095
Grogu. I need you to go
to the control panel.

489
00:53:28.230 --> 00:53:30.162
Remember the buttons
I told you never to touch?

490
00:53:30.297 --> 00:53:31.735
<i>I'm gonna need you
to touch them.</i>

491
00:53:31.870 --> 00:53:34.608
<i>Look for
the ignition relay cutoff.</i>

492
00:53:34.743 --> 00:53:37.335
<i>It's next to
the fuel differential readout.</i>

493
00:53:37.471 --> 00:53:40.214
<i>which is between
the pump compression gauge</i>

494
00:53:40.350 --> 00:53:42.113
<i>and the primary reserve indic</i>

495
00:53:44.684 --> 00:53:46.211
Whoa.

496
00:53:46.347 --> 00:53:48.590
No. Don't touch
the missile battery switch.

497
00:53:48.725 --> 00:53:50.365
<i>That's why there's
a safety guard on it.</i>

498
00:53:50.494 --> 00:53:52.522
<i>Do you see
the fuel readout display?</i>

499
00:53:52.657 --> 00:53:54.160
Remember I showed you that one?

500
00:53:54.295 --> 00:53:55.693
<i>It's on the other side</i>

501
00:53:55.829 --> 00:53:57.898
<i>of the manual control
surface calibration un</i>

502
00:54:00.537 --> 00:54:02.667
I don't think
he knows what he's doing.

503
00:54:24.926 --> 00:54:25.958
Get out.

504
00:54:30.468 --> 00:54:33.302
Get going.
They're shooting at you too.

505
00:54:41.375 --> 00:54:43.576
Good job. buddy. Strap in.

506
00:55:08.069 --> 00:55:09.734
I like this kid.

507
00:55:20.214 --> 00:55:22.318
Come on. Come on.

508
00:55:34.298 --> 00:55:36.127
Get us out of atmosphere
and jump!

509
00:55:36.262 --> 00:55:37.531
Get up here.

510
00:55:37.666 --> 00:55:39.599
I need you to bypass
the exhaust restrictors.

511
00:55:53.013 --> 00:55:55.642
This old junker's
gonna get us killed.

512
00:55:55.777 --> 00:55:57.211
I need more power.

513
00:55:57.347 --> 00:55:59.507
Disable the safety panel
so I can override the limiter.

514
00:55:59.588 --> 00:56:02.257
How? I'm a pilot.
not a meknek.

515
00:56:02.393 --> 00:56:04.724
Just rip out
the whole brain board.

516
00:56:10.090 --> 00:56:11.699
Everything okay up there?

517
00:56:11.835 --> 00:56:13.402
Perfect.

518
00:56:19.742 --> 00:56:22.774
I told you to strap in.
Always wear your seat belt.

519
00:56:32.045 --> 00:56:34.181
Take it easy up there!

520
00:56:40.260 --> 00:56:41.760
There we go.

521
00:58:13.380 --> 00:58:15.182
That doesn't look like a Hutt.

522
00:58:15.317 --> 00:58:17.816
This is Imperial Commander
Janu Coin.

523
00:58:17.951 --> 00:58:21.228
He's full of information and
ready to sing like a Yuzzum.

524
00:58:21.364 --> 00:58:23.023
Isn't that right. Coin?

525
00:58:23.158 --> 00:58:24.627
I demand an attorney be present

526
00:58:24.763 --> 00:58:26.128
if I'm to be questioned.

527
00:58:26.629 --> 00:58:27.828
You see?

528
00:58:27.964 --> 00:58:29.838
He's full of secrets.

529
00:58:30.608 --> 00:58:32.498
You were supposed
to bring back Rotta.

530
00:58:33.401 --> 00:58:35.738
We had an arrangement
with the Twins.

531
00:58:35.873 --> 00:58:37.704
This is your Ace of Staves.

532
00:58:38.540 --> 00:58:40.715
This is who they were
going to lead you to.

533
00:58:41.284 --> 00:58:42.551
And then tip him off.

534
00:58:42.686 --> 00:58:45.378
sell you out and collect
credits from both sides.

535
00:58:46.321 --> 00:58:48.051
Take him away.

536
00:58:52.695 --> 00:58:54.554
Intelligence
has been cultivating

537
00:58:54.689 --> 00:58:57.957
a relationship with the Hutts
for a very long time.

538
00:58:58.092 --> 00:58:59.733
and you crossed them.

539
00:59:01.063 --> 00:59:02.828
The Twins can hold a grudge.

540
00:59:02.964 --> 00:59:04.105
I made a call.

541
00:59:04.241 --> 00:59:05.807
I got you the big prize.

542
00:59:06.376 --> 00:59:08.268
The Twins can rot in hell.

543
00:59:08.404 --> 00:59:09.924
Well. you missed out
on them paying you

544
00:59:09.974 --> 00:59:11.880
a big bounty for their nephew.

545
00:59:12.015 --> 00:59:13.015
Hmm...

546
00:59:13.149 --> 00:59:14.616
So be it.

547
00:59:16.379 --> 00:59:18.343
Well. I'll see if
I can hit up Command

548
00:59:18.478 --> 00:59:20.347
for a fee
for the capture of Coin.

549
00:59:20.482 --> 00:59:23.317
Don't worry about it.
It's on me.

550
00:59:23.920 --> 00:59:25.325
This one got messy.

551
00:59:25.461 --> 00:59:27.090
I'm taking a break.

552
00:59:28.330 --> 00:59:30.027
I understand.

553
00:59:30.825 --> 00:59:32.227
Mando.

554
00:59:34.731 --> 00:59:36.165
Good job.

555
01:01:00.014 --> 01:01:02.254
We're gonna
pull the restrictor plates.

556
01:01:02.288 --> 01:01:04.951
The first one should be
just past the return line.

557
01:01:05.086 --> 01:01:06.520
That's it.

558
01:01:06.656 --> 01:01:09.093
There should be three more.

559
01:01:21.334 --> 01:01:24.009
Okay. okay. Okey-doke.

560
01:01:29.848 --> 01:01:30.848
Okay. okay.

561
01:01:30.914 --> 01:01:32.380
Thanks for coming.

562
01:01:32.915 --> 01:01:34.350
No problem.

563
01:01:34.486 --> 01:01:36.989
I'm looking to make some
performance modifications.

564
01:01:37.124 --> 01:01:38.886
I need to cut out
dead weight for speed.

565
01:01:40.557 --> 01:01:42.797
Pull out anything
that doesn't make her go.

566
01:01:43.433 --> 01:01:44.733
Hey!

567
01:01:44.868 --> 01:01:46.039
Hey. Hey.

568
01:01:46.063 --> 01:01:47.063
No. don't touch me!

569
01:01:47.096 --> 01:01:49.296
Heel.

570
01:01:49.431 --> 01:01:51.129
- The horrible baby.
- The bad baby.

571
01:01:51.264 --> 01:01:53.169
Stay.

572
01:01:53.305 --> 01:01:54.610
I purged the fuel lines.

573
01:01:54.634 --> 01:01:56.310
I wanna remove
all the restrictors

574
01:01:56.446 --> 01:01:57.846
and unplug the exhaust.

575
01:01:57.981 --> 01:02:01.473
- Got it. Yeah. yeah.
- No problem. Yeah. I got it.

576
01:02:01.608 --> 01:02:03.345
- No problem.
- Yeah. Okey-doke.

577
01:02:04.685 --> 01:02:06.117
You wanna go help them?

578
01:02:07.788 --> 01:02:09.520
Do you promise to play nice?

579
01:02:10.888 --> 01:02:12.886
All right. Go.

580
01:02:19.460 --> 01:02:21.000
Don't worry about him.

581
01:02:23.068 --> 01:02:24.799
Little guy's gonna be okay.

582
01:02:26.700 --> 01:02:28.935
Sorry. I found these
in your kitchen.

583
01:02:32.673 --> 01:02:34.673
I was alone when I was his age.

584
01:02:35.376 --> 01:02:37.247
I had to fend for myself.

585
01:02:42.317 --> 01:02:44.286
He's lucky he has you.

586
01:02:44.421 --> 01:02:47.522
Well. you didn't
turn out half bad.

587
01:02:48.658 --> 01:02:52.592
Mmm. Life's messy.
but we do the best we can.

588
01:02:54.032 --> 01:02:55.496
Listen. I called a gunrunner

589
01:02:55.631 --> 01:02:57.366
who agreed to take you
out of the system.

590
01:02:57.501 --> 01:02:59.538
We both know the Twins
will be looking for you.

591
01:02:59.674 --> 01:03:01.200
so you best keep moving.

592
01:03:26.128 --> 01:03:27.566
Thank you. Mando.

593
01:03:27.702 --> 01:03:28.997
It was a fair trade.

594
01:03:29.132 --> 01:03:30.796
Make sure you lay low.

595
01:03:30.932 --> 01:03:33.539
I don't wanna see your name
on my list again.

596
01:03:33.674 --> 01:03:34.867
You have my word.

597
01:03:35.770 --> 01:03:38.374
All right. you take care
of yourself. little guy.

598
01:03:39.577 --> 01:03:42.708
And keep an eye on
your old man. too. all right?

599
01:03:43.683 --> 01:03:44.913
Here you go.

600
01:03:45.049 --> 01:03:47.053
Hang on to these for me.

601
01:04:27.758 --> 01:04:30.459
Let's save the rest of these
for after dinner.

602
01:05:47.839 --> 01:05:49.984
Wake up.

603
01:05:50.008 --> 01:05:51.442
Oh. What? Uh.

604
01:05:51.578 --> 01:05:52.858
- Wake up.
- What's going on?

605
01:05:52.882 --> 01:05:54.214
There's someone out there.

606
01:05:54.349 --> 01:05:55.821
I'll be awake in the morning.

607
01:05:55.845 --> 01:05:57.189
Quiet. Get under the floor.

608
01:06:09.098 --> 01:06:12.561
Wait here.
If I signal. get out.

609
01:06:33.153 --> 01:06:35.683
Shh. Shh. Shh.

610
01:07:23.536 --> 01:07:26.534
Help! It got me! It got me!

611
01:07:26.670 --> 01:07:29.275
Keibu.

612
01:08:37.208 --> 01:08:39.070
Help me! Help!

613
01:09:39.138 --> 01:09:41.539
Ow.

614
01:09:42.945 --> 01:09:45.378
Ow. ow. ow.

615
01:09:47.013 --> 01:09:48.447
Let him go.

616
01:09:55.120 --> 01:09:57.148
Hey. you hungry?

617
01:10:01.127 --> 01:10:02.758
You want a treat?

618
01:10:04.591 --> 01:10:05.856
Here you go.

619
01:10:05.992 --> 01:10:08.060
Good girl.

620
01:10:09.069 --> 01:10:10.069
Come on. Come on!

621
01:10:10.138 --> 01:10:12.101
Uh-oh.

622
01:10:12.236 --> 01:10:13.437
Oh.

623
01:10:33.454 --> 01:10:35.230
Uh-oh.

624
01:10:40.034 --> 01:10:41.764
Who hired you?

625
01:10:42.333 --> 01:10:44.129
Was it the Hutts?

626
01:10:45.338 --> 01:10:47.004
Well. if it was the Hutts.

627
01:10:47.139 --> 01:10:49.139
I'd make sure they're
paying you what you're worth.

628
01:10:49.202 --> 01:10:50.868
But I'm guessing a Kyuzo
is smart enough

629
01:10:51.003 --> 01:10:52.083
to get their money up-front

630
01:12:48.997 --> 01:12:50.925
Nal Hutta.

631
01:12:51.060 --> 01:12:54.468
The Hutts are there.
I don't like it.

632
01:13:14.080 --> 01:13:16.149
Oh! Wow! Oh. I'm coming.

633
01:13:23.665 --> 01:13:25.024
Kid. don't be scared.

634
01:13:25.160 --> 01:13:26.825
Don't be scared.
It's okay. yeah.

635
01:13:26.961 --> 01:13:27.969
Come on. let's go.

636
01:13:28.104 --> 01:13:30.097
Oh...

637
01:13:40.014 --> 01:13:43.183
Oh! Hello!
It's me. it's me! You're here.

638
01:13:43.319 --> 01:13:46.312
You came for me! You found me!

639
01:13:47.348 --> 01:13:49.314
Oh. we thought you were dead.

640
01:13:50.083 --> 01:13:51.489
Mandalorian. he saved me.

641
01:13:51.624 --> 01:13:53.591
Big guy. He's inside there.

642
01:13:53.726 --> 01:13:55.560
Yeah. we got to go and find him

643
01:13:55.696 --> 01:13:57.762
and bring him home for the baby.

644
01:13:59.427 --> 01:14:02.333
The big thing. The big dog.
The big dog. The big...

645
01:14:02.469 --> 01:14:04.703
Oh. oh. It picked me up...

646
01:14:15.551 --> 01:14:18.409
Mando is in there.
In the palace.

647
01:14:30.991 --> 01:14:32.463
Come on. Up. up. up. up.

648
01:14:32.599 --> 01:14:34.700
Come on. baby. You can do it.

649
01:14:42.903 --> 01:14:44.743
Big pipe. huh?

650
01:15:12.998 --> 01:15:14.339
Good shot. baby.

651
01:15:54.617 --> 01:15:57.843
You broke our agreement.

652
01:15:57.978 --> 01:16:00.346
Now you must pay.

653
01:16:12.568 --> 01:16:15.401
Mandalorian steel.

654
01:16:15.537 --> 01:16:19.530
Priceless on the black market.

655
01:16:20.608 --> 01:16:24.069
But worth even more is knowing

656
01:16:24.204 --> 01:16:28.308
we have shamed you forever.

657
01:16:28.444 --> 01:16:31.745
We know the Mandalorian Creed.

658
01:16:31.881 --> 01:16:33.421
You will be outcast

659
01:16:33.556 --> 01:16:37.285
for letting an enemy see
your face.

660
01:16:37.821 --> 01:16:39.550
Not if you all die.

661
01:16:43.090 --> 01:16:46.324
It will bring us ecstasy

662
01:16:46.460 --> 01:16:51.562
to watch
your strong spirit break.

663
01:17:00.611 --> 01:17:02.010
Monsters.

664
01:17:02.146 --> 01:17:03.846
You did this to him.

665
01:17:03.981 --> 01:17:07.154
Rotta would have
died painlessly.

666
01:17:07.290 --> 01:17:09.083
but you betrayed us.

667
01:17:09.219 --> 01:17:13.121
Now he will suffer
for centuries.

668
01:17:13.257 --> 01:17:18.426
You see. Hutts live for
hundreds of years.

669
01:17:19.129 --> 01:17:23.662
Just like
your small. green child.

670
01:17:24.164 --> 01:17:26.168
One day you will die.

671
01:17:26.303 --> 01:17:30.139
and Grogu will be without you
to protect him.

672
01:17:30.274 --> 01:17:34.376
And then.
it will be his turn to suffer.

673
01:22:31.712 --> 01:22:33.646
Uh-oh. Which way?

674
01:24:08.006 --> 01:24:09.340
<i>Dank farrik.</i>

675
01:24:12.581 --> 01:24:14.004
Get out! Go!

676
01:24:15.850 --> 01:24:18.085
Come on. go! Go. go!

677
01:24:32.296 --> 01:24:35.099
- Oh. yeah!
- Wow!

678
01:24:35.234 --> 01:24:36.763
Wait. Wait.

679
01:25:05.066 --> 01:25:07.024
You okay?

680
01:25:12.702 --> 01:25:15.038
- How did you get here?
- We got a ship.

681
01:25:15.174 --> 01:25:16.770
That way. Let's go!

682
01:25:52.772 --> 01:25:54.643
This way. This way. yeah.

683
01:26:06.662 --> 01:26:08.525
This way!

684
01:26:14.827 --> 01:26:16.369
Up. up. up. up. going up!

685
01:26:16.504 --> 01:26:18.667
I don't want to fall.
I don't want to.

686
01:26:19.399 --> 01:26:20.399
Go!

687
01:26:20.506 --> 01:26:22.303
Yeah. Okay. okay. Yeah.
Let's go.

688
01:26:35.224 --> 01:26:37.752
Go. kid.
I can't fit in that thing.

689
01:26:38.960 --> 01:26:40.693
but you have to leave.

690
01:26:43.194 --> 01:26:44.464
Don't worry.

691
01:26:45.067 --> 01:26:46.765
I'll be right behind you.

692
01:26:50.963 --> 01:26:52.836
Go now. I'll hold them off.

693
01:26:53.739 --> 01:26:56.100
We'll come back for you. Mando.

694
01:26:59.738 --> 01:27:00.871
Come on. baby.

695
01:27:01.007 --> 01:27:02.807
Don't worry. We'll be back.

696
01:27:02.942 --> 01:27:05.080
Yeah. let's go. Let's go.

697
01:27:05.216 --> 01:27:06.583
Come on. baby.

698
01:28:37.313 --> 01:28:38.735
Goodbye. kid.

699
01:31:32.781 --> 01:31:34.545
No life force detected.

700
01:37:32.112 --> 01:37:35.112
Methinks you are
the one who stole my fish.

701
01:37:48.723 --> 01:37:51.689
I'm guessing
you're not from around here.

702
01:37:55.432 --> 01:37:58.368
A morsel like you
should be more careful.

703
01:37:58.504 --> 01:38:02.304
You look to be the bottom
of the Nal Hutta food chain.

704
01:38:03.507 --> 01:38:05.469
I'm surprised
you haven't found your way

705
01:38:05.604 --> 01:38:07.639
to the Hutts' supper table.

706
01:38:09.842 --> 01:38:12.149
You've heard of the Hutts.
have you?

707
01:38:13.080 --> 01:38:14.514
Are you scared?

708
01:38:16.117 --> 01:38:17.518
You should be.

709
01:38:17.653 --> 01:38:20.722
They would swallow you whole
given half a chance.

710
01:38:25.193 --> 01:38:27.263
Make yourself scarce.

711
01:38:49.888 --> 01:38:50.888
Uh-huh.

712
01:39:25.857 --> 01:39:27.224
Hey.

713
01:39:28.894 --> 01:39:30.458
Get away from my fish.

714
01:39:35.601 --> 01:39:37.333
Keibu.

715
01:39:57.553 --> 01:39:59.993
The hunter says
you have a partner.

716
01:40:01.259 --> 01:40:04.124
Says you two escaped the Twins.

717
01:40:04.260 --> 01:40:06.395
Well. that's impressive.

718
01:40:11.699 --> 01:40:14.401
Says your partner's
hurt real bad.

719
01:40:14.537 --> 01:40:18.176
Bit by a dragonsnake.
Poisoned.

720
01:40:22.082 --> 01:40:24.512
I want you to feed this to him.

721
01:40:26.721 --> 01:40:27.910
Now. you should know.

722
01:40:28.045 --> 01:40:29.915
this might be too little.
too late.

723
01:40:30.051 --> 01:40:33.290
and there's a good chance
he doesn't wake up.

724
01:40:37.395 --> 01:40:39.327
Either way.
best thing you can do

725
01:40:39.462 --> 01:40:41.762
right now
is make him comfortable.

726
01:40:41.897 --> 01:40:45.467
There comes a time where
we all have to say goodbye.

727
01:40:52.441 --> 01:40:54.909
I wish you luck. small traveler.

728
01:43:42.783 --> 01:43:44.008
Hey. kiddo.

729
01:43:49.419 --> 01:43:50.815
The old protect the young.

730
01:43:50.950 --> 01:43:53.017
and then the young
protect the old.

731
01:43:53.893 --> 01:43:55.393
This is the Way.

732
01:43:58.299 --> 01:44:00.266
Now how do we
get off this planet?

733
01:44:06.969 --> 01:44:10.034
That's the gunrunner
that was carrying Rotta.

734
01:46:24.337 --> 01:46:27.943
Well. kid. the way I see it
we got two choices.

735
01:46:28.680 --> 01:46:31.616
We can use this ship.
Get off world.

736
01:46:31.752 --> 01:46:34.616
That might buy us some time.
A little bit of peace.

737
01:46:34.752 --> 01:46:37.346
But the Hutts
will keep coming for us.

738
01:46:38.182 --> 01:46:40.217
Just like they came for Rotta.

739
01:46:43.096 --> 01:46:44.397
So. do we run?

740
01:46:48.595 --> 01:46:49.699
Or do we fight?

741
01:47:33.479 --> 01:47:35.547
Huh?

742
01:47:53.124 --> 01:47:54.731
Roger. roger!

743
01:47:56.861 --> 01:47:58.031
Affirmative.

744
01:48:07.245 --> 01:48:08.580
Follow my lead.

745
01:48:12.843 --> 01:48:14.146
Fire!

746
01:48:24.890 --> 01:48:26.598
Come on. Come on.

747
01:49:05.170 --> 01:49:07.034
On me.

748
01:49:50.513 --> 01:49:51.540
Fall back!

749
01:52:30.102 --> 01:52:31.744
Go help Rotta.

750
01:52:39.847 --> 01:52:41.512
You saw my face.

751
01:52:44.217 --> 01:52:45.648
Now it's time to die.

752
01:53:54.453 --> 01:53:55.751
Leave him alone!

753
01:56:44.698 --> 01:56:45.723
Keibu.

754
01:57:21.567 --> 01:57:24.498
We don't have much time.
We have to get out of here.

755
01:57:25.267 --> 01:57:26.399
Is there another way out?

756
01:57:26.535 --> 01:57:29.470
- I think it's that way.
- Go. Go!

757
01:57:45.823 --> 01:57:46.982
Target sighted.

758
01:58:12.750 --> 01:58:14.175
Hello?

759
01:58:14.311 --> 01:58:15.491
<i>Mando! We came back.</i>

760
01:58:15.515 --> 01:58:16.853
- What?
- We came back.

761
01:58:16.988 --> 01:58:18.690
We told you we would.

762
01:58:25.596 --> 01:58:29.391
<i>Adelphi Squadron.
entering atmosphere.</i>

763
01:58:29.526 --> 01:58:32.533
- What's your status. Mando?
- <i>We're under attack.</i>

764
01:58:33.301 --> 01:58:34.500
There are too many.

765
01:58:34.636 --> 01:58:37.065
Fire everything you have
at my location.

766
01:58:38.268 --> 01:58:41.372
- <i>Your location?</i>
- Yes. my location.

767
01:58:41.508 --> 01:58:43.043
I can't give that order.

768
01:58:43.178 --> 01:58:44.710
Don't worry...

769
01:58:46.485 --> 01:58:49.077
we'll be out of here
by the time you do.

770
01:58:50.547 --> 01:58:51.547
Good luck.

771
01:58:55.059 --> 01:58:56.625
Blue Leader to squadron.

772
01:58:56.761 --> 01:58:59.927
<i>assume defensive formation.
prepare to engage.</i>

773
01:59:00.062 --> 01:59:01.126
All weapons hot.

774
01:59:01.261 --> 01:59:02.365
Copy that.

775
01:59:19.810 --> 01:59:21.346
Enemy fighters approaching.

776
01:59:23.756 --> 01:59:24.756
Here they come.

777
01:59:51.885 --> 01:59:53.275
Turbolasers. up ahead.

778
01:59:53.411 --> 01:59:54.582
Got it.

779
02:00:15.272 --> 02:00:17.033
I've got one on my tail.

780
02:00:19.570 --> 02:00:21.213
I got you.

781
02:00:31.091 --> 02:00:32.715
Yippee! Yay!

782
02:00:32.850 --> 02:00:34.556
Taking out the launch tubes.

783
02:00:41.930 --> 02:00:45.270
Blue Leader to Red Jammer.
mark it and lock it in.

784
02:00:47.632 --> 02:00:48.768
Locking in target.

785
02:00:52.307 --> 02:00:53.575
It's a dead end.

786
02:00:54.772 --> 02:00:56.347
We're trapped.

787
02:00:56.882 --> 02:00:58.250
Stand back.

788
02:01:04.315 --> 02:01:05.827
<i>We're closing fast.</i>

789
02:01:05.851 --> 02:01:07.114
Repeat. we're closing fast.

790
02:01:07.250 --> 02:01:08.859
You better be
out of there. Mando.

791
02:01:08.995 --> 02:01:10.259
Jump.

792
02:01:10.395 --> 02:01:12.588
That's a long way down.

793
02:01:12.723 --> 02:01:13.928
Closing on target.

794
02:01:15.131 --> 02:01:17.693
- Gotta jump.
- Moat's not that deep.

795
02:01:17.829 --> 02:01:19.795
It's a bomber. Jump.

796
02:01:19.931 --> 02:01:21.999
Let's light up this swamp.

797
02:01:56.409 --> 02:01:58.310
<i>Anybody got eyes on Mando?</i>

798
02:01:58.845 --> 02:01:59.874
There they are.

799
02:02:04.150 --> 02:02:08.177
Zeb. go collect the trash.

800
02:02:15.861 --> 02:02:18.926
I'm getting a little tired
of these hot extractions.

801
02:02:19.729 --> 02:02:21.733
What took you so long?

802
02:02:23.066 --> 02:02:24.099
Hop in.

803
02:02:24.234 --> 02:02:26.338
Let's head home.

804
02:02:49.026 --> 02:02:50.560
Colonel.

805
02:02:52.799 --> 02:02:54.289
Messy.

806
02:02:54.758 --> 02:02:56.192
Very messy.

807
02:02:57.137 --> 02:02:58.565
Why'd you come for me?

808
02:02:58.701 --> 02:03:00.528
That wasn't part of the mission.

809
02:03:01.331 --> 02:03:04.668
You were right.
Coin told us everything.

810
02:03:04.804 --> 02:03:06.235
The Twins were playing us.

811
02:03:06.370 --> 02:03:09.172
Feeding information
to the Empire all along.

812
02:03:10.241 --> 02:03:13.341
They picked a side.
It wasn't ours.

813
02:03:13.476 --> 02:03:17.485
Besides.
we don't leave our own behind.

814
02:03:17.620 --> 02:03:19.386
I'm an independent contractor.

815
02:03:19.522 --> 02:03:22.618
Sure. Mando. Sure you are.

816
02:03:33.231 --> 02:03:35.098
Can I give you a ride somewhere?

817
02:03:35.234 --> 02:03:38.100
Actually. I was thinking
I could stay here.

818
02:03:38.236 --> 02:03:40.411
Maybe work for the New Republic.

819
02:03:40.547 --> 02:03:43.005
Don't take this
the wrong way. but...

820
02:03:43.140 --> 02:03:45.114
I'm not sure you would fit in.

821
02:03:45.250 --> 02:03:47.045
You know...

822
02:03:47.180 --> 02:03:49.620
I might have
a uniform that would fit him.

823
02:03:50.423 --> 02:03:53.557
Come on. let me buy you a drink.

824
02:03:55.155 --> 02:03:57.720
Thank you. Mando.
I owe you big time.

825
02:03:57.855 --> 02:03:59.524
Just doing my job.

826
02:03:59.660 --> 02:04:00.863
And keep an eye on him.

827
02:04:01.733 --> 02:04:03.559
Your dad's one of the good ones.

828
02:04:17.974 --> 02:04:19.081
Come on. big guy.

829
02:04:20.084 --> 02:04:23.081
Watch your step.
First round's on me.

830
02:04:31.989 --> 02:04:34.029
Hey. kid. Come up here.

831
02:04:53.814 --> 02:04:55.212
Your turn.

832
02:04:57.914 --> 02:04:59.150
Go ahead.

832
02:05:00.305 --> 02:06:00.288
